<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
Entitlements for Verbinal (slim). No bundled Python, no notebook, no subprocess
spawning, so we can run with the minimum modern-sandbox profile.

  app-sandbox                               — required for MAS; hardens direct
                                              distribution too.
  network.client                            — CADC / VOSpace HTTPS calls.
  files.user-selected.read-write            — NSOpenPanel / NSSavePanel for
                                              FITS downloads and research exports.
  files.downloads.read-write                — default save target for
                                              research observations.
  keychain-access-groups                    — CADC auth token + credentials.

Intentionally NOT present (dropped from the Pi entitlements when this branch
diverged; re-add only if you reintroduce features requiring them):
  cs.disable-library-validation             — only needed when loading
                                              non-platform-signed dylibs.
  cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory       — only needed for Python C extensions.
  cs.allow-jit                              — only needed for JIT'd numerical code.
  inherit                                   — only needed when spawning subprocesses.
  files.all                                 — overbroad, never needed for this app.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.files.downloads.read-write</key>
    <true/>
    <!--
    Two keychain-access-groups:
      1. $(AppIdentifierPrefix)com.codebg.Verbinal — app-default group; keeps
         compatibility with tokens written by pre-addon-family builds.
      2. A4ABW5VD88.codebg.verbinal.family — shared with official Verbinal
         addons (first: Verbinal Pi at com.codebg.Verbinal.addon.notebook).
         `AppState.init` points `KeychainStorage.configure(accessGroup:)` at
         this string so writes/reads route through the shared group and the
         CADC token is visible to Pi without a second sign-in.

    Note for MAS release: the "Verbinal MAS" provisioning profile must be
    regenerated at developer.apple.com to include the
    A4ABW5VD88.codebg.verbinal.family access group. Apple Development
    automatic signing in Debug handles the new group without manual steps.
    -->
    <key>keychain-access-groups</key>
    <array>
        <string>$(AppIdentifierPrefix)com.codebg.Verbinal</string>
        <string>A4ABW5VD88.codebg.verbinal.family</string>
    </array>
</dict>
</plist>
